        <header>
            <h1>Kalavad (Shitala) Town</h1>
            <p>A Municipality in Jamnagar District, Gujarat</p>
        </header>
        
        <p>
            **Kalavad** is a key administrative and commercial town, serving as the headquarters for Kalavad Taluka. It is centrally located in the Saurashtra region.
        </p>

        <h2>Key Town Facts</h2>
        <div class="fact-box">
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Jamnagar District, Gujarat, India.</p>
            <p><strong>Taluka Headquarters:</strong> Kalavad (Shitala).</p>
            <p><strong>Economy:</strong> Primarily agricultural trading and local commerce.</p>
            <p><strong>Connectivity:</strong> Well-connected by state highways to Rajkot, Jamnagar, and Gondal.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Administrative Details</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>**Municipality:** Kalavad is governed by a local municipality.</li>
            <li>**Assembly Constituency:** It falls under the Kalavad Assembly Constituency.</li>
            <li>**Primary Crops:** Cotton, groundnut, and various oilseeds are traded in its markets.</li>
        </ul>
